WEBVTT

00:00.855 --> 00:03.791
[music playing]

00:07.445 --> 00:12.445
Subtitles by explosiveskull

00:14.000 --> 00:20.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

00:23.379 --> 00:24.446
Trick or treat.

00:45.904 --> 00:46.738
[scream]

00:50.742 --> 00:53.843
Mom, why do we
watch these movies?

00:53.845 --> 00:57.380
Maybe because we're
not supposed to.

00:57.382 --> 00:59.549
And they're fun.

00:59.551 --> 01:01.953
I thought these
movies were scary.

01:01.955 --> 01:05.756
They are... so scary
that most people would

01:05.758 --> 01:07.893
close their eyes or run away.

01:07.895 --> 01:09.895
But we don't.

01:09.897 --> 01:12.330
When the shadows are dark,
and the music is creepy,

01:12.332 --> 01:17.401
and you know you should close
your eyes, we take a peek...

01:17.403 --> 01:23.743
boo!... and laugh
because now you know.

01:23.745 --> 01:25.812
Know what?

01:25.814 --> 01:29.481
That you're stronger than
anything you're afraid of.

01:29.483 --> 01:30.786
Pretty cheesy, Mom.

01:34.356 --> 01:35.923
I'm going to
check in on Jeanie.

01:35.925 --> 01:37.156
OK.

01:37.158 --> 01:40.027
You two continue to
scare yourself silly.

01:40.029 --> 01:41.129
Thanks, babe.

01:43.566 --> 01:44.733
Chocolate milk?

01:44.735 --> 01:45.568
Yeah.

01:55.947 --> 01:58.850
[suspenseful music playing]

02:28.347 --> 02:29.281
[muffled scream]

02:37.390 --> 02:38.258
Mom?

02:40.660 --> 02:42.698
No jumping out at me, OK?

02:46.735 --> 02:47.599
Mom?

02:47.601 --> 02:50.604
[suspenseful music playing]

03:10.359 --> 03:11.459
FATHER: Honey?

03:11.461 --> 03:12.295
Dax?

03:16.365 --> 03:17.364
Dax!

03:17.366 --> 03:18.101
[gunshot]

03:18.103 --> 03:19.836
Don't look, Dax.

03:19.838 --> 03:20.772
Don't look!

03:27.879 --> 03:28.712
[gunshot]

03:40.592 --> 03:43.662
[rock music playing]

04:14.495 --> 04:15.563
Easy boy, Karloff.

04:22.671 --> 04:23.703
"Blood feast."

04:23.705 --> 04:26.439
It actually sounds
kind of boring.

04:26.441 --> 04:28.675
Boring?
Come on, Sis.

04:28.677 --> 04:30.145
"Blood Feast" is
a Herschell Gordon

04:30.147 --> 04:31.880
Lewis cinematic classic, OK?

04:31.882 --> 04:34.715
Blood Fest, the thing
that I'm going to,

04:34.717 --> 04:39.121
is the greatest horror
event of all time.

04:39.123 --> 04:40.122
It's gonna suck.

04:40.124 --> 04:41.991
Whatever, Jayme.

04:41.993 --> 04:43.026
DR. CONWAY: Dax?

04:43.028 --> 04:46.728
Will you come to
my office, please?

04:46.730 --> 04:48.231
(MUMBLING) Hey,
shut the fuck up.

04:48.233 --> 04:49.100
Cheers!

05:00.880 --> 05:04.951
Hey, you, uh,
wanting to see me?

05:09.056 --> 05:11.488
You know, I'm being
interviewed on Network News

05:11.490 --> 05:12.224
tonight.

05:12.226 --> 05:13.124
It's kind of a big deal.

05:13.126 --> 05:14.393
I really want you to be there.

05:16.696 --> 05:18.264
Yeah.
Yeah, sure.

05:18.266 --> 05:19.932
I... I'll, uh, I'll try to come.

05:19.934 --> 05:24.036
I'm going to be talking
about Blood Fest...

05:24.038 --> 05:27.907
how I and my family are
totally opposed to it,

05:27.909 --> 05:34.780
how no child of mine would
ever set foot on those grounds.

05:34.782 --> 05:36.250
You understand?

05:36.252 --> 05:37.918
Mm-hmm.

05:37.920 --> 05:39.987
Good.

05:39.989 --> 05:42.791
Then, uh, you won't
be needing this.

05:48.764 --> 05:50.098
Wait a minute, I...

05:50.100 --> 05:52.200
look, I think I'm old enough
to make my own decision.

05:52.202 --> 05:55.070
You live in my house.

05:55.072 --> 06:00.242
I don't understand this
obsession with violence, Dax.

06:00.244 --> 06:02.810
Dad, it's... it's movies.

06:02.812 --> 06:03.878
I don't know what to tell you.

06:03.880 --> 06:06.316
It poses as
entertainment, but it's

06:06.318 --> 06:10.619
these kind of movies that drove
my patient to kill your mother.

06:10.621 --> 06:12.721
How do you not see that?

06:12.723 --> 06:13.824
This isn't about her.

06:16.761 --> 06:20.097
Please, don't... don't do that.

06:20.099 --> 06:23.200
Blood Fest is a gathering
of freaks and degenerates

06:23.202 --> 06:27.939
celebrating mindless
violence and gore.

06:27.941 --> 06:29.707
ANTHONY WALSH: Blood
Fest is the gathering

06:29.709 --> 06:31.709
of freaks and
degenerates celebrating

06:31.711 --> 06:33.911
mindless violence and gore.

06:33.913 --> 06:36.114
It's going to be extraordinary!

06:36.116 --> 06:37.015
ANNOUNCER: Blood!

06:37.017 --> 06:37.615
Blood!

06:37.617 --> 06:39.717
Blood Fest!

06:39.719 --> 06:41.853
Legendary field
producer, movie promoter,

06:41.855 --> 06:44.958
and lover of all things
horrific, Anthony Walsh,

06:44.960 --> 06:48.094
invites you to
run for your life!

06:48.096 --> 06:49.561
Blood Fest!

06:49.563 --> 06:52.165
ANTHONY WALSH: We've taken a
700-acre ranch in the middle

06:52.167 --> 06:55.668
of nowhere and recreated
the most iconic

06:55.670 --> 06:57.804
of cinematic horror locales.

06:57.806 --> 06:59.806
Don't miss the biggest
names in horror,

06:59.808 --> 07:03.177
celebrity panels, and the
most outrageous parties.

07:03.179 --> 07:06.281
Recent additions include
the Original Arborist, Roger

07:06.283 --> 07:08.916
Hinckley, the cast and
crew of "Hell's Nest,"

07:08.918 --> 07:13.021
and late night karaoke
with Zachary Levi.

07:13.023 --> 07:16.657
Get inside the gates before
sundown Halloween night.

07:16.659 --> 07:17.659
ANNOUNCER (ON COMPUTER): Blood!

07:17.661 --> 07:18.626
Blood!

07:18.628 --> 07:20.029
Blood Fest!

07:20.031 --> 07:22.999
Brought to you by
Walsh Corporation.

07:23.001 --> 07:25.001
You've got to
stop watching that.

07:25.003 --> 07:27.669
You're torturing yourself.

07:27.671 --> 07:29.305
We'll find another ticket.

07:29.307 --> 07:31.341
The whole thing has
been sold out for months.

07:31.343 --> 07:34.244
Scalpers are charging more
money than I have pores.

07:34.246 --> 07:35.278
Yo!
Yo!

07:35.280 --> 07:36.380
Yo!

07:36.382 --> 07:37.880
Y'all see my Overwatch post?

07:37.882 --> 07:42.253
I hacked the game code, got
all badass on ultimate skills.

07:42.255 --> 07:43.920
Three new subscribers.

07:43.922 --> 07:45.323
None of them relatives.

07:45.325 --> 07:48.192
Boom, boom, bah.

07:48.194 --> 07:49.526
Morning, Krill.

07:49.528 --> 07:51.062
I'm now ready to forsake
my virtual multiverses

07:51.064 --> 07:53.898
for a weekend of Blood Fest.

07:53.900 --> 07:55.267
Plus, I think it's
time that I find

07:55.269 --> 07:58.736
the extraordinary lady worthy
enough to de-flower me,

07:58.738 --> 08:00.205
the Krill.

08:00.207 --> 08:02.207
It's mind boggling that no
one has snatched you up yet.

08:02.209 --> 08:03.775
I know, right?
That's what I'm saying.

08:03.777 --> 08:05.009
It's crazy out here.

08:05.011 --> 08:05.878
It's crazy out here
in this world, man.

08:05.880 --> 08:08.348
Where... what... what... what...

08:08.350 --> 08:10.350
what's up with him?

08:10.352 --> 08:12.751
His dad found his wristband.

08:12.753 --> 08:15.121
You guys just go
ahead without me.

08:15.123 --> 08:16.021
Maybe you should call Ashley.

08:16.023 --> 08:17.157
She could probably get you in.

08:17.159 --> 08:18.359
Oh, please don't
mention her, dude.

08:18.361 --> 08:19.226
There's a "Hell's Nest"
panel at Blood Fest.

08:19.228 --> 08:20.263
She probably has an extra pass.

08:22.298 --> 08:23.696
I... I... I can't...

08:23.698 --> 08:24.931
I can't believe... It's so wrong.

08:24.933 --> 08:28.402
Ashley Spats... Ashley
Spats is at Blood Fest.

08:28.404 --> 08:29.770
And I'm stuck here.

08:29.772 --> 08:32.340
You know, Ashley who thought
"Black Christmas" was

08:32.342 --> 08:34.275
a Tyler Perry holiday movie.

08:34.278 --> 08:36.777
You know, sh... sh... she refuses
to watch "Seven," because she

08:36.779 --> 08:37.778
didn't see the first six.

08:37.780 --> 08:38.846
OK.

08:38.847 --> 08:40.347
She thought that
"28 Days Later"

08:40.350 --> 08:42.318
was a... was a health doc about
the fucking menstrual cycle.

08:42.320 --> 08:43.921
Dax, you're pitiful.

08:46.291 --> 08:48.957
Here's something
that you really want,

08:48.959 --> 08:53.430
and you're going to
let your dad stop you?

08:53.432 --> 08:55.399
He's a... he's a scary guy.

08:55.401 --> 08:58.168
Everyone's dad is a scary guy.

08:58.170 --> 08:59.769
Nut up.

08:59.771 --> 09:01.039
You were made for Blood Fest.

09:05.412 --> 09:07.811
Blood Fest.

09:07.813 --> 09:09.780
I'll call her.

09:09.782 --> 09:10.881
You happy?

09:10.883 --> 09:11.917
Yeah.

09:15.020 --> 09:17.523
That's what I'm talking about!

09:17.525 --> 09:20.024
Pow!

09:20.026 --> 09:22.095
[cell phone ringing]

09:23.897 --> 09:24.896
Dax.
DAX (ON PHONE): Hey!

09:24.898 --> 09:25.663
Ashley!

09:25.665 --> 09:27.065
Long time no nothing.

09:27.067 --> 09:28.833
DAX (ON PHONE): I just
wanted to congratulate you on

09:28.835 --> 09:31.338
your new movie, "Hell's Nest."

09:31.340 --> 09:35.007
Looks like it's
going to be awesome.

09:35.009 --> 09:37.977
So you're... you're a...
you're an actor in it, right?

09:37.979 --> 09:40.447
You're... oh, God... wha...
wha... what are you...

09:40.449 --> 09:41.915
what are you playing again?

09:41.917 --> 09:42.983
Topless girl number four.

09:42.985 --> 09:44.918
Topless girl number
four, that's it.

09:44.920 --> 09:45.952
It's a key role.

09:45.954 --> 09:48.054
It's no topless
girl number three.

09:48.056 --> 09:50.090
I'd kill for topless
girl number three.

09:50.092 --> 09:51.325
Well, you're in a movie.

09:51.327 --> 09:52.460
That's awesome.

09:52.462 --> 09:53.661
You're making your
dreams come true.

09:53.663 --> 09:56.265
Uh, if you need, uh,
a ride to... uh, to...

09:56.267 --> 09:58.467
Blood Fest, you're more
than welcome to, uh...

09:58.469 --> 10:02.371
Uh, I'm actually here already,
you know, to emotionally

10:02.373 --> 10:03.871
prepare for the fans.

10:03.873 --> 10:06.509
I'm trying to find a way in.

10:06.511 --> 10:09.912
They have more barbed wire
here than an S&M summer camp.

10:09.914 --> 10:12.881
Wait, Ashely, the...
the reason I'm calling...

10:12.883 --> 10:13.749
What's taking him so long?

10:13.751 --> 10:15.218
Why doesn't he just ask her?

10:15.220 --> 10:16.985
I've known Dax a long time.

10:16.987 --> 10:18.556
He survived some hard stuff.

10:18.558 --> 10:20.823
And he's got his pride.

10:20.825 --> 10:22.193
Dax is not going a
coward just so he can...

10:22.195 --> 10:24.495
Please, Ashley, just...
just get me through the door!

10:24.497 --> 10:28.097
I'm literally on my
knees begging you, look.

10:28.099 --> 10:29.367
That's me begging.

10:29.369 --> 10:30.468
Do you get it?

10:30.470 --> 10:31.168
Scratch that.

10:31.170 --> 10:33.137
He's cookie dough.

10:33.139 --> 10:36.006
Let's go to Blood Fest!

10:36.008 --> 10:37.942
SAM: Why all the rules?

10:37.944 --> 10:41.213
Freddy only kills in
dreams, virgins survive.

10:41.215 --> 10:43.549
Michael won't just build a
dirty bomb and kill them all.

10:43.551 --> 10:44.450
These rules.

10:44.452 --> 10:46.184
DAX: You've got to have rules.

10:46.186 --> 10:47.886
Otherwise, death
would be random...

10:47.888 --> 10:49.921
just chaotic and meaningless.

10:49.923 --> 10:51.324
SAM: That's life.

10:51.326 --> 10:53.527
DAX: If movies were life,
no one would buy a ticket.

10:53.529 --> 10:56.365
[music playing]

11:04.105 --> 11:06.274
ANNOUNCER: Blood Fest gates
are closing in one minute!

11:06.276 --> 11:07.040
Come on!

11:07.042 --> 11:07.609
The gates are closing!

11:07.611 --> 11:09.044
Let's go!

11:12.549 --> 11:16.417
This is gonna be the
best night of my life.

11:16.419 --> 11:17.386
SAM: Come on, Dax!

11:17.388 --> 11:20.957
[music playing]

11:53.327 --> 11:56.461
Please have your
wristbands on and visible.

11:56.463 --> 11:57.663
This is so beautiful.

11:57.665 --> 12:00.064
It's like some twisted
and horrific heaven.

12:00.066 --> 12:03.602
Tone it back, boys.

12:03.604 --> 12:05.237
Hi.

12:05.239 --> 12:06.106
Hey.

12:11.945 --> 12:13.245
Wristband.

12:13.247 --> 12:15.348
I'm actually supposed to
be meaning someone here.

12:15.350 --> 12:16.081
Dax.

12:16.083 --> 12:17.351
Oh, she's right there.

12:17.353 --> 12:18.084
Whoa.

12:18.086 --> 12:18.719
LENJAMIN: Oh, it's cool.

12:18.721 --> 12:21.622
He's with me.

12:21.624 --> 12:23.089
Thanks.

12:23.091 --> 12:24.391
Ashley, you are a lifesaver.

12:24.393 --> 12:27.628
This is Lenjamin Cain,
director of "Hell's Nest."

12:27.630 --> 12:29.128
He's why you're here.

12:29.130 --> 12:30.964
Thanks, baby.

12:30.966 --> 12:31.965
Appreciate it.

12:31.967 --> 12:32.835
Uh-huh.

12:36.440 --> 12:37.339
It's my pleasure.

12:37.341 --> 12:38.573
It's my pleasure to help out.

12:38.575 --> 12:42.378
Uh, babe, I'm sorry,
but why is this fanboy

12:42.380 --> 12:44.012
getting in under my name?

12:44.014 --> 12:45.481
He's a friend.

12:45.483 --> 12:48.617
And besides, you did it for
me, your little pooky pokey

12:48.619 --> 12:49.719
pooky bear.

12:49.721 --> 12:51.487
LENJAMIN: Oh, yeah?
ASHLEY: Yeah.

12:51.489 --> 12:52.521
Rawr.

12:52.523 --> 12:53.255
LENJAMIN: Pooky
bear needs a poke?

12:53.257 --> 12:55.625
I'm a naughty bear.

12:55.627 --> 12:57.059
Uh, OK.

12:57.061 --> 13:00.196
Uh, well, thanks very much
for getting me in, Lenjamin.

13:00.198 --> 13:01.665
And congratulations on the film.

13:01.667 --> 13:03.232
Oh, thank you so much.

13:03.234 --> 13:04.401
It's... it's shit.

13:04.403 --> 13:06.637
It's the shit.

13:06.639 --> 13:08.071
It's the shit.

13:08.073 --> 13:11.007
I left out that article.

13:11.009 --> 13:14.177
I got to ask you to leave.

13:14.179 --> 13:15.112
I'm messing with you.

13:15.114 --> 13:16.213
Oh, OK.

13:16.215 --> 13:17.348
I'm messing with you.

13:17.350 --> 13:18.684
Yeah, you're going
to love the film.

13:18.686 --> 13:19.451
When it comes out,
everybody's going to love it.

13:19.453 --> 13:22.086
Ashley's great in it.

13:22.088 --> 13:23.522
- Stacked.
- Really?

13:23.524 --> 13:24.590
We need to go.

13:24.592 --> 13:26.057
Namaste.

13:26.059 --> 13:27.559
OK.

13:27.561 --> 13:30.697
That was awkward.

13:30.699 --> 13:32.197
That's my balloons.

13:32.199 --> 13:35.568
[music playing]

13:35.570 --> 13:37.236
Clown Town?

13:37.238 --> 13:38.003
That's not even funny.

13:38.005 --> 13:39.706
We're not going there.

13:39.708 --> 13:41.039
We're going everywhere, dude.

13:41.041 --> 13:42.342
You don't like clowns?

13:42.344 --> 13:44.512
You know I don't like clowns!

13:44.514 --> 13:47.450
[music playing]

13:51.487 --> 13:52.422
Nice balloons.

13:57.828 --> 14:00.060
She's the one.

14:00.062 --> 14:02.631
She's the one I will
lay with tonight.

14:02.633 --> 14:03.832
SAM: Lucky girl.

14:03.834 --> 14:04.566
Someone should tell her.

14:04.568 --> 14:05.603
KRILL: Why do you joke?

14:08.673 --> 14:09.806
Oh, my God...

14:09.808 --> 14:10.673
the Arborist.

14:10.675 --> 14:11.841
SAM: Whoa, he trimmed the beard.

14:11.843 --> 14:12.608
KRILL: Dax, you've
got to go meet him.

14:12.610 --> 14:14.278
It's the Arborist!

14:16.246 --> 14:21.552
Roger Hinckley, you, sir,
are the scariest man alive.

14:21.554 --> 14:23.654
Hey, check it out.

14:23.656 --> 14:25.489
I got a, uh, tattoo.

14:25.491 --> 14:26.590
Oh.

14:26.592 --> 14:28.057
Arbor Day?

14:28.059 --> 14:31.763
Between you and me though, part
four is my favorite, all right?

14:31.765 --> 14:33.230
Never saw it.

14:33.232 --> 14:35.767
Part four?

14:35.769 --> 14:38.202
Never saw any of them.

14:38.204 --> 14:41.306
You've never seen
any of your own films?

14:41.308 --> 14:44.142
I don't like scary movies, OK?

14:44.144 --> 14:45.310
It's too much gore.

14:45.312 --> 14:49.247
The sight of blood
just makes me want to...

14:49.249 --> 14:50.651
I used to puke after every take.

14:54.623 --> 14:55.956
Wou... would it
be too much to ask

14:55.958 --> 15:00.159
if you'd possibly do the
Arborist catchphrase for me?

15:00.161 --> 15:01.162
Yeah.

15:03.130 --> 15:03.998
It would be.

15:08.872 --> 15:10.337
Hey, a big fan.

15:10.339 --> 15:13.273
I actually disemboweled you in a
modded version of Mortal Kombat

15:13.275 --> 15:14.276
the other day.

15:17.180 --> 15:18.246
Um, dude, let's go.

15:18.248 --> 15:19.550
The kick-off party's
about to start.

15:25.421 --> 15:27.689
Asshole.

15:27.691 --> 15:30.158
DAX: That was devastating.

15:30.160 --> 15:32.194
SAM: Never meet your heroes.

15:32.196 --> 15:35.698
It's always a letdown.

15:35.700 --> 15:37.165
This should cheer you up.

15:37.167 --> 15:40.168
[cheering]

15:40.170 --> 15:43.576
[music playing]

15:47.479 --> 15:55.921
Ten, nine, eight, seven, six,
five, four, three, two, one!

15:55.923 --> 15:57.523
[applause]

16:05.900 --> 16:07.467
[applause]

16:09.403 --> 16:12.337
I've got a question!

16:12.339 --> 16:15.775
Who wants some horror!

16:15.777 --> 16:16.778
[applause]

16:20.583 --> 16:25.586
Inside these gates,
we have re-created all

16:25.588 --> 16:28.321
your cinematic scare-scapes...

16:28.323 --> 16:32.760
from summer camps to
asylums to circuses!

16:32.762 --> 16:33.962
Clowns, not the clowns.

16:33.964 --> 16:37.966
Every monster or maniac
to ever spill blood

16:37.968 --> 16:40.367
on the silver screen
has been granted

16:40.369 --> 16:43.237
a portion of these grounds.

16:43.239 --> 16:46.474
And it's all for you.

16:46.476 --> 16:50.345
I want this man to adopt me.

16:50.347 --> 16:55.417
But children... children,
we have a problem.

16:55.419 --> 16:58.520
Horror is dead.

16:58.522 --> 17:00.389
I mean, look around you!

17:00.391 --> 17:02.491
Our vampires glitter!

17:02.493 --> 17:05.796
Our zombies have become
soap opera stars!

17:05.798 --> 17:11.935
Our slashers have
grown dull and old.

17:11.938 --> 17:14.371
We put Freddy on a lunchbox!

17:14.373 --> 17:17.608
We put Lovecraft
in a coloring book!

17:17.609 --> 17:21.545
We have overconsumed
and overproduced,

17:21.547 --> 17:27.318
and we have taken what was
forbidden, what was dangerous,

17:27.319 --> 17:29.423
and we have made it common.

17:36.296 --> 17:37.864
Wanna make movies scary again?

17:37.866 --> 17:41.367
[cheering]

17:41.369 --> 17:42.568
Wanna do it tonight?

17:42.570 --> 17:43.971
Yeah!

17:43.973 --> 17:47.710
Wanna make a horror movie
to end all horror movies?

17:51.781 --> 17:53.782
