Well, I got here early, and
the doors were still shut.

22:58.380 --> 23:01.114
And there was this
yellow warehouse

23:01.116 --> 23:02.848
thing with a back door.

23:02.850 --> 23:05.386
It was sealed shut, but
some guy gave me this,

23:05.388 --> 23:06.819
and it opened right up.

23:06.821 --> 23:07.687
It's not going to open now.

23:07.689 --> 23:08.588
The whole place is locked down.

23:08.590 --> 23:11.824
Hey, this a crypto-processor.

23:11.826 --> 23:13.327
We use this on Doomlarp!

23:13.329 --> 23:14.294
Doomlarp?

23:14.296 --> 23:16.030
Jesus!
Geek!

23:16.032 --> 23:17.032
Fuck!

23:17.034 --> 23:18.932
I can hack this.

23:18.934 --> 23:21.069
If you get me to the back
gate, I'll get it open.

23:21.071 --> 23:22.404
We can do this.

23:22.406 --> 23:23.937
Sorry.

23:23.939 --> 23:28.276
It's on the other side of the
grounds near the circus stuff.

23:28.278 --> 23:30.879
My God!
Fucking Clown Town!

23:30.881 --> 23:32.083
Are you fucking serious?

23:35.786 --> 23:39.821
All right, so, we are
by the main entrance.

23:39.823 --> 23:40.956
Clown Town is here.

23:40.958 --> 23:43.093
Yeah, we just gotta move quick.

23:43.095 --> 23:43.859
Stay quiet.

23:43.861 --> 23:45.362
You have flashlights?

23:45.364 --> 23:47.963
I always have flashlights.

23:47.965 --> 23:51.767
So you want to hike through
700 acres of nightmare filled

23:51.769 --> 23:54.704
with those pig fuck
butchers and any other freak

23:54.706 --> 23:57.075
that Walsh has cooked
up for the slim chance

23:57.077 --> 24:00.844
that Mr. Robot here can
hack open a back door.

24:00.846 --> 24:02.480
You got any other plans?

24:02.482 --> 24:03.814
Uh, you turds go and get help.

24:03.816 --> 24:05.716
Me and Ashley are staying
here where it's safe.

24:05.718 --> 24:06.884
What?

24:06.886 --> 24:08.387
DAX: No, we can't do that.
It's a bad idea.

24:08.389 --> 24:11.989
Wa... Walsh said
follow the rules.

24:11.991 --> 24:13.358
What rules?

24:13.360 --> 24:15.026
Dude, ru... rules of the
genre, rules of the subgenres,

24:15.028 --> 24:16.962
the tropes, the principles.

24:16.964 --> 24:19.998
Rule number one is... is
don't split up, dude.

24:20.000 --> 24:22.901
You... you seen a film before?

24:22.903 --> 24:25.003
I don't see movies.

24:25.005 --> 24:27.739
I make them.

24:27.741 --> 24:29.176
Babe, I got a signal.

24:29.178 --> 24:31.010
911 DISPATCHER (ON PHONE):
911, what's your emergency?

24:31.012 --> 24:32.513
Uh, yeah, I'm at Blood Fest.

24:32.515 --> 24:34.013
We're trapped on the
festival grounds,

24:34.015 --> 24:36.150
and people are
being slaughtered.

24:36.152 --> 24:38.818
I need immediate
assistance for two people.

24:38.820 --> 24:40.387
911 DISPATCHER (ON PHONE):
We have your location.

24:40.389 --> 24:42.290
Someone is on the way.

24:42.292 --> 24:43.592
Thank you very much.

24:43.594 --> 24:46.194
My name is Lenjamin Cain,
and I'm a film director.

24:46.196 --> 24:47.429
And I'm a celebrity.

24:47.431 --> 24:48.762
And I'm with an
up-and-coming actress, so...

24:48.764 --> 24:50.232
- Coming actress.
- I'm with the coming actress.

24:50.234 --> 24:52.334
So if that will speed things
up at all, that would be great.

24:52.336 --> 24:53.101
911 DISPATCHER (ON
PHONE): Stay calm.

24:53.103 --> 24:54.137
Remain where you are.

24:54.139 --> 24:57.275
And if you can,
go fuck yourself.

25:00.445 --> 25:01.977
What was that?

25:01.979 --> 25:03.312
911 DISPATCHER (ON PHONE): If
you are able and so inclined,

25:03.314 --> 25:07.950
put your penis between your
legs and into your anus.

25:07.952 --> 25:10.387
Then proceed to fuck yourself.

25:10.389 --> 25:11.854
And how would that help us?

25:11.856 --> 25:13.022
No one's coming.

25:13.024 --> 25:14.158
911 DISPATCHER (ON
PHONE): Oh, don't worry.

25:14.160 --> 25:15.925
Someone should be
there any moment.

25:15.927 --> 25:19.062
[chainsaw revving]

25:19.064 --> 25:20.097
[screams]

25:20.099 --> 25:20.797
Move!
Move!

25:20.799 --> 25:21.466
Go!
Go!

25:21.468 --> 25:22.534
Go!
Go!

25:22.536 --> 25:23.468
Go!
Come on!

25:23.470 --> 25:24.435
Through the door!

25:24.437 --> 25:26.103
Don't rush me!

25:26.105 --> 25:28.574
Anything else I
can assist you with?

25:28.576 --> 25:31.477
Thank you for using 911.

25:31.479 --> 25:33.345
So that was a pleasant start.

25:33.347 --> 25:35.581
Billy, I want you to
double-check the outer fences,

25:35.583 --> 25:38.082
get the voltage up to 700-plus.

25:38.084 --> 25:40.118
Amy, let's talk Clown Town.

25:40.120 --> 25:42.222
I want to see those
freaks all riled up.

25:42.224 --> 25:43.689
They're riled up, sir.

25:43.691 --> 25:45.925
OK, make sure you catch any
call that tries to get out.

25:45.927 --> 25:47.460
But on a few of
them, play it cool.

25:47.462 --> 25:50.530
I at least put some people to
think that help is on the way.

25:50.532 --> 25:52.332
Why?

25:52.334 --> 25:56.069
I mean, doesn't it seem
kind of cruel just to give

25:56.071 --> 25:57.307
people a false sense of hope?

26:03.979 --> 26:07.349
What if I told you that
you were going to die

26:07.351 --> 26:10.586
tonight no matter what you did?

26:10.588 --> 26:13.222
What would you feel?

26:13.224 --> 26:14.523
Despair.

26:14.525 --> 26:16.858
Despair.

26:16.860 --> 26:19.395
Now what if I told
you, you had a chance

26:19.397 --> 26:23.466
but only, only if you made all
the right calls, only if you

26:23.468 --> 26:26.168
took all the right
steps, only you

26:26.170 --> 26:29.406
dug down deep inside
your soul and you

26:29.408 --> 26:34.578
found some hidden strength
you never even knew you had?

26:34.580 --> 26:35.847
How would you feel then?

26:38.284 --> 26:40.552
Motivated.

26:40.554 --> 26:42.886
Motivation.

26:42.888 --> 26:44.190
It's what every character needs.

26:47.294 --> 26:50.896
[music playing]

26:55.436 --> 26:57.969
DAX: I'm telling you, there
are rules you have to follow,

26:57.971 --> 26:59.904
like don't chant
anything in Latin.

26:59.906 --> 27:01.039
Don't get naked.

27:01.041 --> 27:02.441
