32:26.928 --> 32:28.294
How's it going, guys?

32:28.296 --> 32:29.562
Need anything?

32:29.564 --> 32:30.931
Doritos?
Red Bull?

32:30.933 --> 32:32.032
Corn syrup?

32:32.034 --> 32:34.001
No, but these
super real graphics

32:34.003 --> 32:35.501
are hella cheesing, my dude.

32:35.503 --> 32:37.603
Also, my guys are moving slow.

32:37.605 --> 32:39.940
Well... he's a zombie.

32:39.942 --> 32:42.877
Yeah, that's boring.

32:42.879 --> 32:44.679
When are we going
to play the victims?

32:44.681 --> 32:45.913
Soon.

32:45.915 --> 32:46.914
I promise.

32:46.916 --> 32:49.485
[zombies growling]

32:50.854 --> 32:51.853
DAX: Oh, shit!

32:51.855 --> 32:54.555
Here they come!

32:54.557 --> 32:56.493
[banging]

32:59.864 --> 33:02.865
OK, yeah, got it.

33:02.867 --> 33:05.436
[suspenseful music]

33:16.515 --> 33:17.416
Excuse me...

33:22.487 --> 33:23.422
Oh, shit.

33:28.528 --> 33:29.460
Uh...

33:29.462 --> 33:30.796
You have to hit
him in the head!

33:30.798 --> 33:31.830
I'm not going to hit a corpse!

33:31.832 --> 33:33.564
That's disgusting!

33:33.566 --> 33:34.434
Oh, my God!

33:38.538 --> 33:39.137
Oh!

33:39.139 --> 33:40.374
Oh, my God!

33:46.748 --> 33:47.747
Get away!

33:47.749 --> 33:48.513
Oh, my God!

33:48.515 --> 33:49.581
How's it coming, Dax?

33:49.583 --> 33:52.652
Blue, green,
red, another red...

33:52.654 --> 33:54.654
- instructions maybe.
- Do something!

33:54.656 --> 33:56.123
There's too many wires!
All right?

33:56.125 --> 33:57.057
Which one do I pull?

33:57.059 --> 33:58.025
It's not a bomb!

33:58.027 --> 33:59.793
Just pull them all!

33:59.795 --> 34:05.100
George Romero, if you're
out there, save us.

34:05.102 --> 34:06.669
[panting]

34:10.072 --> 34:11.472
What?

34:11.474 --> 34:12.239
Yo!

34:12.241 --> 34:14.074
That's some bullshit!

34:14.077 --> 34:15.610
A... are there autosaves?

34:18.547 --> 34:19.380
Oh!

34:19.382 --> 34:20.750
- They're dead?
- Oh!

34:20.752 --> 34:21.516
Fuck!

34:21.518 --> 34:22.518
They were dead before!

34:26.123 --> 34:26.856
Come on.

34:26.858 --> 34:27.989
We gotta get moving.

34:27.992 --> 34:28.992
Let's... let's go!

34:28.994 --> 34:30.226
Quick

34:30.228 --> 34:34.063
Question do you mind
if I just tag along?

34:34.065 --> 34:35.264
Are you... are you kidding?

34:35.266 --> 34:38.434
Well, it just occurs
to me that the guy

34:38.436 --> 34:41.806
that gets left behind is
usually the next one to bite it.

34:41.808 --> 34:43.841
I mean, at least that's
the Arborist's MO.

34:43.842 --> 34:45.976
Huh, you have seen the movies.

34:45.978 --> 34:47.011
I read the scripts...

34:47.013 --> 34:47.880
once.

34:52.485 --> 34:55.719
Everyone deserves a
chance at redemption.

34:55.722 --> 34:57.956
Come on.

34:57.958 --> 35:00.527
[music playing]

35:04.800 --> 35:06.132
Billy!

35:06.134 --> 35:08.835
I'm going to need you to
fix that zombie transmitter.

35:08.837 --> 35:11.436
While you're at it,
add a few extra dead.

35:11.438 --> 35:13.472
God knows we have the corpses.

35:13.474 --> 35:15.774
Sir, may I remind
you your partner

35:15.776 --> 35:19.113
didn't authorize any repairs
after the first death?

35:19.115 --> 35:22.183
Yes, but he's
not here right now.

35:22.185 --> 35:23.616
And I am.

35:23.618 --> 35:26.086
And I'm trying to make a movie!

35:26.088 --> 35:28.190
Huh?

35:28.192 --> 35:29.557
Cultists!

35:29.559 --> 35:30.292
Go wide!

35:30.294 --> 35:31.059
Go wide on the cultists!

35:31.061 --> 35:31.893
Yeah, yeah, yeah yeah.

35:31.895 --> 35:34.029
Now smash cut to the yeti.

35:34.031 --> 35:35.496
Oh, good.

35:35.498 --> 35:37.464
You see how you juxtapose the
two, and you tell a story?

35:37.466 --> 35:38.499
Oh, my God!

35:38.501 --> 35:40.535
He is eating her face!

35:40.537 --> 35:41.137
Oh!

35:41.139 --> 35:42.004
Oh, my God!

35:42.006 --> 35:44.106
That is deliciously disgusting.

35:44.108 --> 35:45.241
Oh!

35:45.243 --> 35:47.475
How do you do all this?

35:47.477 --> 35:49.045
Like how do you get
all these participants?

35:49.047 --> 35:51.881
Oh, it took a lot of work...

35:51.883 --> 35:52.715
years of it.

35:52.717 --> 35:56.086
I found some scary people.

35:56.088 --> 35:58.856
And the homicidal maniacs?

35:58.858 --> 36:03.793
You take a clinically damaged
mind, you force him to watch

36:03.795 --> 36:06.496
one movie continuously.

36:06.498 --> 36:12.036
Eventually, the movie mythos
becomes the man's mythos.

36:12.038 --> 36:18.010
Eventually, the movie world
becomes the man's world.

36:18.012 --> 36:23.648
You tell him he's
Leatherface, he's Leatherface.

36:23.650 --> 36:25.817
The clowns I found
on Craigslist.

36:25.819 --> 36:29.222
Uh, hey, sorry
about your boyfriend.

36:29.224 --> 36:31.892
He wasn't my boyfriend...

36:31.894 --> 36:34.060
not really.

36:34.062 --> 36:36.196
Next time a director's
casting couch is a futon,

36:36.198 --> 36:38.231
I'm walking the other way.

36:38.233 --> 36:39.433
Futon?

36:44.673 --> 36:47.841
Kind of reminds me of April
Showers from Arbor Day 4.

36:47.843 --> 36:51.245
10 years ago, there was the
Arbor Day massacre, right?

36:51.247 --> 36:54.715
And Hodderton High has
still not recovered.

36:54.717 --> 36:56.751
So spring break at
Hodderton High, right?

36:56.753 --> 36:59.154
School is closed, but the
botany class stays behind

36:59.156 --> 37:02.124
for some extracurricular fun.

37:02.126 --> 37:05.827
God, this is some of the best
kills of the series, man.

37:05.829 --> 37:09.798
I mean, that one where you
drown that guy in a tub of sap.

37:09.800 --> 37:10.432
Fuck!

37:10.434 --> 37:11.633
I mean, shit!

37:11.635 --> 37:13.970
That was horrifying!

37:13.972 --> 37:16.040
So slow.

37:16.042 --> 37:17.840
So sticky.

37:17.842 --> 37:20.044
That was my idea.

37:20.046 --> 37:20.978
What?

37:20.980 --> 37:22.012
Oh, yeah.

37:22.014 --> 37:23.479
The director, he
wanted to move on.

37:23.481 --> 37:26.749
He wanted to just smash some
skulls, keep going... faster.

37:26.751 --> 37:29.753
I said, no, no, no,
let's slow this down, OK?

37:29.755 --> 37:35.193
Because the arborist would
take his time, like a tree.

37:35.195 --> 37:36.294
I knew it.

37:36.296 --> 37:38.196
Knew what?

37:38.198 --> 37:40.299
I knew that you knew
more about the films

37:40.301 --> 37:42.600
than you were letting on.
Come on, dude!

37:42.602 --> 37:44.036
Just do the catchphrase
for me once!

37:44.038 --> 37:45.037
Please!
Just once!

37:45.039 --> 37:46.105
Come on!
I hate Arbor Day.

37:46.107 --> 37:47.406
You don't!
How can you hate it?

37:47.408 --> 37:49.442
I mean, you go to these
conventions all the time.

37:49.444 --> 37:51.077
You did six films
for fuck's sake!

37:51.079 --> 37:53.246
I am an actor, OK?

37:53.248 --> 37:55.748
- I'm a serious actor.
- You guys?

37:55.750 --> 37:59.019
Arbor Day was my
first fucking movie.

37:59.021 --> 37:59.852
Somebody said me, "Hey, Roger.

37:59.854 --> 38:00.988
You want to wear a mask?"

38:00.990 --> 38:02.222
I said, "A mask?

38:02.224 --> 38:02.990
Are you kidding?

38:02.992 --> 38:04.392
I want to see my face!

38:04.394 --> 38:08.029
I want to see my God damn
face on that big screen!"

38:08.031 --> 38:11.299
If I had hidden my face, I
would've been able to move on.

38:11.301 --> 38:12.833
But, no.

38:12.835 --> 38:17.306
No, this is the
face of tree horror.

38:17.308 --> 38:18.207
Guys!

38:18.209 --> 38:19.308
Guys!

38:19.310 --> 38:21.644
I... I... I think
someone's watching us!

38:26.217 --> 38:27.284
Fuck me.

38:31.356 --> 38:34.024
[music playing]

38:34.026 --> 38:35.025
Ah!

38:35.027 --> 38:36.326
Oh, my God!

38:36.328 --> 38:38.328
Oh, my God!

38:38.330 --> 38:40.164
[zombie growling]

38:40.166 --> 38:41.034
[screaming]

38:42.035 --> 38:42.966
Go!

38:42.968 --> 38:43.967
Go!

38:43.969 --> 38:44.934
Oh, my God!

38:44.936 --> 38:47.271
Ah!

38:47.273 --> 38:48.938
Did you see that guy?

38:48.940 --> 38:49.841
Oh, my God!

38:58.718 --> 39:00.385
You played that guy?

39:00.387 --> 39:02.387
Why is he so much
bigger than you?

39:02.389 --> 39:03.822
I lost a lot of
weight, all right?

39:03.824 --> 39:06.325
Plus, I have a thyroid issue.

39:06.327 --> 39:07.559
I used to just eat a lot.

39:07.561 --> 39:10.263
Wait, did you guys
see where Krill went?

39:10.265 --> 39:11.763
He... he got away.

39:11.765 --> 39:12.664
He went the other direction.

39:12.666 --> 39:14.200
We should get in.
Come on.

39:14.202 --> 39:15.634
It's Hodderton High.

39:15.636 --> 39:17.237
You killed like 12 people
here in the original film.

39:17.239 --> 39:18.105
I didn't kill anybody!

39:18.107 --> 39:20.340
OK, let's just get inside!

39:20.342 --> 39:23.709
Hey, that's... that's
not such a good idea.

39:23.711 --> 39:25.245
We don't have a choice, Dax!

39:25.247 --> 39:26.082
Did you watch the movie?

39:28.951 --> 39:30.118
Hello!

39:30.120 --> 39:31.252
Wait, there's someone inside!

39:31.254 --> 39:32.287
Come on!
Come on!

39:32.289 --> 39:33.321
Come on!

39:33.323 --> 39:34.255
Thank you.

39:34.257 --> 39:35.223
Thank you!

39:35.225 --> 39:37.125
Oh, thank you!

39:37.127 --> 39:39.327
Wait, I know you.

39:39.329 --> 39:40.329
You're Zachary Levi.

39:40.331 --> 39:42.131
The karaoke guy?

39:42.133 --> 39:44.166
Listen, I think we're
going to safe, all right?

39:44.168 --> 39:45.468
The windows are all secured.

39:45.470 --> 39:46.402
The door is locked.

39:46.404 --> 39:48.137
Flynn Ryder!

39:48.139 --> 39:50.206
You're Flynn fucking Ryder!

39:50.208 --> 39:51.340
You've never
seen a single film,

39:51.342 --> 39:52.975
but you've seen "Tangled."

39:52.977 --> 39:53.809
Maybe.

39:53.811 --> 39:55.878
Are you... are you alone?

39:55.880 --> 39:57.380
I was...

39:57.382 --> 39:59.416
I was... I was with my friends,
some of my closest friends.

39:59.418 --> 40:01.418
We stuck together
when things got nutty.

40:01.420 --> 40:03.286
We made it through the woods.

40:03.288 --> 40:05.123
And then we were
attacked by these

40:05.125 --> 40:07.258
crazed cannibal hillbillies.

40:07.260 --> 40:08.493
They tracked us down.
They hunted us.

40:08.495 --> 40:10.228
They were killing and
eating my friends...

40:10.230 --> 40:12.296
I think about
Flynn Ryder a lot.

40:12.298 --> 40:16.033
I mean... a lot.

40:16.035 --> 40:18.137
It was the saddest,
most terrifying

40:18.139 --> 40:19.271
thing I've ever witnessed.

40:19.273 --> 40:20.506
Like, I couldn't believe...

40:20.508 --> 40:24.108
When Flynn smolders
at Rapunzel, I felt...

40:24.110 --> 40:25.712
I don't know... humid.

40:28.316 --> 40:30.450
There's this one gi... there
was a girl that I loved...

40:30.452 --> 40:31.884
actually, she was
the love of my life...

40:31.886 --> 40:32.751
and I didn't have a chance
to tell her, because we were

40:32.753 --> 40:34.052
trying to run to the school.

40:34.054 --> 40:36.289
Right before we got in the
door, they grabbed her.

40:36.291 --> 40:37.357
And they started
to tear her apart.

40:37.359 --> 40:38.191
- My hair is magical.
- It was...

40:38.193 --> 40:40.561
Well, sometimes magical.

40:40.563 --> 40:42.263
OK, let's focus.

40:42.265 --> 40:44.198
I'm so sorry
about your friends.

40:44.200 --> 40:45.366
Is this place safe?

40:45.368 --> 40:47.168
Like I said, the
windows were all sealed,

40:47.170 --> 40:48.402
and I've locked all the doors.

40:48.404 --> 40:50.970
Without this key right
here, there's no way in.

40:50.972 --> 40:52.274
Or out.

40:52.276 --> 40:53.776
Well, of course, but we
wouldn't want to go out...

41:01.083 --> 41:04.353
Flynn Ryder!

41:04.355 --> 41:05.956
[screaming]

41:08.992 --> 41:10.359
The classroom.

41:10.361 --> 41:11.229
Go, go, go, go go!

41:16.235 --> 41:17.401
Oh, my God.

41:17.403 --> 41:18.368
Oh, my God!

41:18.370 --> 41:19.238
Oh, my God!

41:21.507 --> 41:22.805
[MUSIC - SMASH MOUTH, "ALL
STAR"]

41:22.807 --> 41:27.511
Somebody once told me the
world is gonna roll me.

41:27.513 --> 41:29.280
I ain't the sharpest
tool in the shed.

41:29.282 --> 41:30.648
Yo!
What up, dude?

41:30.650 --> 41:32.517
Welcome to the party, bro!
GUY: What's up, dude?

41:32.519 --> 41:33.218
Don't you know
what's going on?

41:33.220 --> 41:34.385
People are dying!

41:34.387 --> 41:35.286
It's Blood Fest, dude!

41:35.288 --> 41:36.354
GUY: Fucking Blood Fest, bro.

41:36.356 --> 41:39.022
No, I mean actually
getting killed.

41:39.024 --> 41:42.026
Walsh made everything real...
the monsters, everything.

41:42.028 --> 41:43.596
Oh, really?

41:43.598 --> 41:48.367
He's created werewolves,
ghosts, vampires.

41:48.369 --> 41:49.867
Oh, yeah.

41:49.869 --> 41:51.403
It sounds like somebody dipped
into the K-2 a little early.

41:51.405 --> 41:53.138
[laughter]

41:53.140 --> 41:55.642
Dork.

41:55.644 --> 41:57.577
If we don't get that key,
we're not going out of here.

41:57.579 --> 42:01.414
I am not going to be
murdered by the Arborist!

42:01.416 --> 42:04.217
That is just too fucking ironic!

42:04.219 --> 42:07.187
Every... every answer is
in the origin story, right?

42:07.189 --> 42:09.024
Jason's drowning,
Freddy's burning.

42:13.028 --> 42:13.628
I got it.

42:13.630 --> 42:15.597
Tommy Wakes.

42:15.599 --> 42:18.400
- Tommy who?
- Tommy.

42:18.402 --> 42:19.434
You!
The Arborist.

42:19.436 --> 42:21.035
Oh, sure.
Good.

42:21.037 --> 42:22.103
Guys...

42:22.105 --> 42:23.338
So your dad was
the school arborist,

42:23.340 --> 42:25.507
and you watched as some
teenagers accidentally

42:25.509 --> 42:27.943
killed your father
and then used a wood

42:27.945 --> 42:29.312
chipper to bury the body.

42:29.314 --> 42:30.779
Jesus.

42:30.781 --> 42:36.386
Yeah, you grew up alone in
the woods, raised by the trees.

42:36.388 --> 42:38.153
Is... is that in the movie?

42:38.155 --> 42:38.920
It's implied.

42:38.922 --> 42:40.391
What about that scar?

42:40.393 --> 42:42.293
What about that alien mark that
shows that I'm their spawn?

42:42.295 --> 42:43.126
No, no, no, no.

42:43.128 --> 42:44.528
That's part five, mistake.

42:44.530 --> 42:46.563
In part six, they pretend
it never happened, right?

42:46.565 --> 42:47.298
Faster.

42:47.300 --> 42:48.732
OK, uh, all right.

42:48.734 --> 42:53.538
You are solely killing to
avenge your father's death.

42:53.540 --> 42:54.271
I'm not lying.

42:54.273 --> 42:56.374
It... it... it's true.

42:56.376 --> 42:58.576
Walsh somehow made
monsters real.

42:58.578 --> 42:59.877
I don't know how
to explain this.

42:59.879 --> 43:05.150
Well, I suppose vampires
would be simple enough.

43:05.152 --> 43:06.485
There's a way out...

43:06.487 --> 43:07.753
a back gate.

43:07.755 --> 43:08.953
If I could just get to
the others, we'll be...

43:08.955 --> 43:10.489
You would just lure
girls from Eastern

43:10.491 --> 43:17.163
Europe with promises of visas
and high-paying American jobs.

43:17.165 --> 43:20.667
Uh, yeah, I mean,
America's great for that.

43:20.669 --> 43:24.203
And then you would
surgically sharpen their teeth.

43:24.205 --> 43:27.374
And you would chemically
stimulate glands,

43:27.376 --> 43:31.244
so they produce abnormal
amounts of pheromones,

43:31.246 --> 43:34.917
making them sexually
irresistible.

43:38.521 --> 43:40.622
Wow.

43:40.624 --> 43:42.524
You are really pretty.

43:42.526 --> 43:47.563
And then finally, you would
infect them with a chronic case

43:47.565 --> 43:48.998
of porphyria.

43:55.306 --> 43:57.005
Wh... what is that?

43:57.007 --> 44:00.443
It's a rare disease
resulting in insomnia,

44:00.445 --> 44:05.383
heightened sensitivity to light,
and an unquenchable thirst

44:05.385 --> 44:07.418
for blood.

44:07.420 --> 44:09.453
Is that a real thing?

44:09.455 --> 44:10.322
Look it up.

44:16.430 --> 44:19.398
[screaming]

44:19.400 --> 44:20.266
Oh.

44:24.605 --> 44:27.607
I... I'm sorry.

44:27.609 --> 44:30.777
I... I'm not going to stay.

44:30.779 --> 44:33.513
You're such a neat girl.

44:33.515 --> 44:36.582
I really would love to stay here
and maybe have sex with you.

44:36.584 --> 44:37.483
I really would.

44:37.485 --> 44:38.352
I just...

44:41.089 --> 44:43.657
You've never be with a woman.

44:43.659 --> 44:45.126
Not in person, no.

44:49.230 --> 44:53.066
Look, my friends are out
there, and they might need me.

44:53.068 --> 44:53.701
Oh!

44:53.703 --> 44:56.403
Such loyalty!

44:56.405 --> 44:59.707
Such innocence.

44:59.709 --> 45:00.742
You could come with us.

45:00.744 --> 45:03.210
I mean, maybe...
there's a way out.

45:03.212 --> 45:04.480
- No, get away.
- No, don't.

45:04.482 --> 45:05.380
- Please...
- No!

45:05.382 --> 45:07.215
Go!

45:07.217 --> 45:08.584
OK.

45:08.586 --> 45:09.485
Go!

45:09.487 --> 45:10.353
I'm sorry.

45:13.458 --> 45:14.324
I suck with girls.

45:22.634 --> 45:24.166
So here's what
you're gonna do.

45:24.168 --> 45:28.171
You are going to distract him
by pretending to be his dad.

45:28.173 --> 45:29.640
- Whose dad?
- Your dad.

45:29.642 --> 45:30.541
My dad.

45:30.543 --> 45:33.210
Yeah, his dad.

45:33.212 --> 45:38.749
He's, uh, he's a... he's a
complicated character, right?

45:38.751 --> 45:43.755
A tragic soul, a ghostly
patriarch reaching out

45:43.757 --> 45:45.791
to his troubled son.

45:45.793 --> 45:48.794
It's Hamlet's father.

45:48.796 --> 45:50.363
It's the role you
were born to play.

46:17.594 --> 46:18.461
Son.

46:25.434 --> 46:29.339
I am so... so proud of you.

46:32.175 --> 46:38.213
You have avenged me, honored me.

46:38.215 --> 46:43.654
You have ripped up all
the diseased roots.

46:43.656 --> 46:47.456
You've thrashed all the weeds.

46:47.458 --> 46:51.796
You've cleared the garden
of all the fickle growth

46:51.798 --> 46:54.366
so that a true tree may thrive!

46:56.903 --> 47:00.272
That tree is you.

47:03.343 --> 47:04.509
He's amazing.

47:04.511 --> 47:10.883
My son, you may rest now.

47:10.885 --> 47:14.385
Your work is done.

47:14.387 --> 47:15.791
Give me the trimmer.

47:25.701 --> 47:28.669
That's it.

47:28.671 --> 47:31.371
Well done, Timmy.

47:31.373 --> 47:32.840
Tommy.

47:32.842 --> 47:33.774
Tommy.

47:33.776 --> 47:34.777
[growls]

47:37.981 --> 47:41.582
Hey, tree hugger!

